      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MARSHAL LEE ROSE (1) is a talented type and proved too classy last time to win by 1.5 lengths at Sale in a handy 24.68 beating Miss My Brother. Looks to have an edge on most of these. ASTON GOZO (7) has a strong record this track and trip with five wins and six placings from 14 starts. Hit the frame latest (28.55) when third at Bendigo in a Grade 5. Looks well placed here and among the chances. NIGHTTIME (2) doesn't have the best strike-rate. Hit the board with a minor placing last time when second (28.54) at Bendigo. Solid record at the distance winning two races. Expected to feature again. MACKENZIE ROSE (8) is worth consideration after filling a hole from the same draw last start.",
